TI  - An automatic ontology construction approach for BIM-IoT semantic integration in intelligent operation and maintenance of high-speed railway stations
PY  - 2025
JO  - Engineering Research Express
DO  - 10.1088/2631-8695/ae1c92
AB  - The operation and maintenance (O&M) of high-speed railway stations in the field of Architecture, Engineering and Construction (AEC) require efficient data integration from multi-source heterogeneous data, including Building Information Modeling (BIM) data and Internet of Things (IoT) sensor data. However, due to differences in data formats, semantic levels, and temporal scales, the seamless integration of BIM and IoT data remains a significant challenge. To address this issue, this paper proposes a Web Ontology Language (OWL)-based semantic ontology automatic construction method for BIM and IoT data integration. By utilizing predefined rules and dynamic processing mechanisms, the proposed method efficiently extracts semantic ontology from both BIM and IoT data, thereby solving the semantic interoperability problem and minimizing the inefficiency of manual ontology construction. To validate the effectiveness of the method, simulation experiments were conducted using BIM data of a high-rise building and synthetic virtual IoT sensor data in the integrated O&M scenario of Shenzhenbei Railway Station. The results demonstrate that the proposed method can automatically generate ontology models that effectively support intelligent O&M, proving its feasibility and practical applicability in real-world scenarios. © 2025 IOP Publishing Ltd. All rights, including for text and data mining, AI training, and similar technologies, are reserved.
