TY  - JOUR
TI  - A Secure Multimodal Retrieval Framework for Consumer Electronics under AI-driven Attacks
PY  - 2025
JO  - IEEE Transactions on Consumer Electronics
DO  - 10.1109/tce.2025.3643172
AB  - In the field of consumer electronics, multimodal retrieval systems are increasingly employed to support intuitive product search based on a combination of reference images and natural language queries. However, such systems are vulnerable to AI-driven attacks, including adversarial prompts and manipulated inputs that can mislead retrieval outcomes. To address this, we propose SHRC-Net, a secure and robust multimodal image retrieval framework that integrates Semantic Harmonization and Region Composition. The architecture comprises three core modules: a Semantic Harmonization Unit (SHU) that aligns textual semantics with fine-grained visual regions, an Adaptive Region Composer (ARC) that captures region-level dependencies under semantic guidance, and a Unified Training Objective (UTO) that incorporates alignment, attention regularization, and compositional classification losses. SHRC-Net builds target-aware representations that faithfully reflect user intent while enhancing resistance to adversarial manipulations. The framework is trained end-to-end without requiring additional annotations. Experiments on multiple benchmark datasets demonstrate that SHRC-Net achieves state-of-the-art retrieval performance, while also exhibiting strong robustness against ambiguous or malicious queries. These results underscore its potential for secure deployment in AI-powered consumer electronics systems. © 1975-2011 IEEE.
