AB  - Database schema matching is a core task in data integration, which involves finding the mapping relationship between tables and attributes between two databases. However, this task is very challenging due to structural heterogeneity and semantic differentiation. Although many studies have explored solutions, they often suffer from low accuracy, poor generality, and the inability to provide pre-training data. In this paper, we propose a method named PMFTA, which is based on the combination of schema information and instance information to realize database schema relationship matching. This method uses a variety of database information and pattern matching methods, introduces attention mechanism and deep learning technology, and effectively solves the generality problem of processing logic for part of missing data, as well as the precision problem of processing large string matching and semantic ambiguity. Using this method can improve the accuracy and generality of overall pattern matching, and there is no need to prepare pre-training data in advance. After experimental comparison, using two versions of the real database of an enterprise, compared with other algorithms, the accuracy can be improved in the scenario of missing database description, and it still has good robustness in the case of missing other partial data. © 2024 IEEE.
