TY  - CONF
TI  - CISKGG: A Collective Intelligence Strategy for Heterogeneous Knowledge Graph Generation for Criminology as a Domain of Choice
PY  - 2022
JO  - 2022 IEEE International Conference for Women in Innovation, Technology and Entrepreneurship, ICWITE 2022 - Proceedings
DO  - 10.1109/icwite57052.2022.10176264
AB  - Knowledge Graph (KG) generation is a promising problem which has to be tackled in the era of Web 3.0 as the web is moving towards a more intelligent and organized semantic web. This paper proposes a framework for KG generation for criminology as a prospective domain of choice. The proposed model uses two distinct deep learning classifiers namely the Transformers and Gated Recurrent Units (GRUs) to classify the dataset and the generated metadata respectively. A static upper domain ontology is also made use of as a reference ontology to aggregate and grow the knowledge base. Knowledge and instance aggregation is achieved using Wikidata and Moki as standard prospective knowledge stores along with the Latent Dirichlet allocation (LDA) based topic modelling. This framework also generates the ontologies dynamically using OntoColab and the alignment of static and dynamic ontologies is achieve using the Lin Similarity measure with a specified threshold. The encompassment of entities from a News API knowledge stack, which integrates five different news APIs, helps in further enrichment of entities as well as instances. The Second Order Cooccurrence Pointwise Mutual Information (SOC-PMI) measure with the Goodall Index with variation in thresholds and differential step deviance measures ensures relevant information filtering and the Fish School Search with APMI helps in instance alignment along with the optimization of the feasible solution set to a much more optimal solution set to formulate the finalized highly relevant KG. This proposed CISKGG framework achieves an overall precision of 97.02 with the lowest FDR of 0.03. © 2022 IEEE.
