PY  - 2020
JO  - CEUR Workshop Proceedings
AB  - Database integration plays a crucial role in understanding the healthcare domain. In this work, a semantic integration methodology was adapted to the birth and mortality database systems of the Brazilian Unified Health System. A case study was carried out to develop a health indicator in the context of maternal and child health in the municipality of Säo Paulo. Three layers of ontologies were created for the solution, containing specifications and mappings. The ontologies were populated and evaluated for their ability to answer competence questions elected by domain experts. The solution proved to be useful in the integration process, presenting a global view of the data and their relationships. © 2020 CEUR-WS. All rights reserved.
