AB  - Military operations are in constant need of up-to-date information about the mission environment. For mission planning, rehearsal, and continuous decision support, detailed information is required on the terrain surface as well as all natural and man-made features. Our research aims to provide the military with a detailed 3D representation of these elements. In this paper, we present how electro-optical remote sensing data acquired by airborne platforms can be exploited to automatically model the mission environment. Our focus is on a model mining approach that aligns with the principles of generative neuro-symbolic artificial intelligence by integrating deep learning-based data analysis with a priori knowledge-based symbolic reasoning: a combination of artificial and real intelligence. We illustrate the approach by automatically extracting a power line infrastructure model from point cloud data. © COPYRIGHT SPIE. Downloading of the abstract is permitted for personal use only.
