AB  - This article aims to investigate DDoS (Distributed Denial of Service) identification techniques in software-defined network (SDN) systems by using DeNSAINet-an emerging AI (Artificial Intelligence) framework that leverages Neuro-Symbolic AI. Neuro-Symbolic AI is a cutting-edge technique that offers better performance when detecting DDoS attacks in an SDN system. In the application of DDoS attack detection, the framework is divided into symbolic reasoning and neural networks. Symbolic reasoning is used to determine whether a particular traffic is normal or malicious, and neural AI based on a knowledge graph is designed to specifically differentiate between DDoS attacks and other types of attacks. We have considered a benchmark dataset, namely InSDN, collected from Kaggle to conduct this research. Our performance metrics remain high, with an accuracy of 99.8% for detecting Metasploit DDoS attacks. The evaluation of other performance parameters was conducted using precision, recall, F1-score, and a confusion matrix. © 2025 IEEE.
