AB  - This research introduces an innovative neurosymbolic fusion approach for cognitive threat reasoning in cyber deception scenarios. The approach integrates data-driven and interpretative logic-based methodologies to identify, anticipate, and address intricate cyber adversaries. It accomplishes this through the utilization of deep neural networks for pattern recognition combined with symbolic reasoning. The system utilizes transparency and resilience in knowledge graphs and probabilistic logic, while employing reinforcement learning for the dynamic optimization of diverse deception methods. Our approach outperforms traditional models in detection accuracy, forecasting adversarial behavior, and generalizing gained knowledge to previously unseen attacks. The model maintains response times and resource use at acceptable levels, facilitating practical application. This study promotes intelligent cyber defense by introducing an adaptive, transparent, and scalable methodology to improve deception-based cybersecurity systems. © 2025 IEEE.
