PY  - 2025
JO  - Proceedings of Machine Learning Research
AB  - Recent hardware accelerators for graph learning have largely overlooked knowledge graph reasoning (KGR), which demands more complex models and longer training times than typical graph tasks. Existing approaches rely on single or distributed GPUs to accelerate translational embedding models, but these general-purpose solutions lag in handling reinforcement learning-based KGR. To address this gap, we introduce KGAccel, the first domain-specific accelerator for RL-based KGR on FPGA. We develop a knowledge-graph compression method and propose a resource-aware mechanism that enables high-speed training even on smaller FPGAs. KGAccel achieves up to 65× speedup over CPU, 8× over GPU, and over 30× higher energy efficiency. © 2025 H. Chen. ML Research Press. All rights reserved.
