AB  - In this paper we investigate automated annotation of tabular data using semantic technologies in combination with neural network embedding. Specifically, we propose an anchoring model in which property and cell types from the data embedding space are aligned with ontology relation and entity types. We show that by combining the power of symbolic reasoning, neural embeddings, and loss function design, a significant performance improvement as high as 86% for column property, 82% for column type, and 87% for column qualifier annotations can be achieved based on DBpedia and Wikidata table extractions. © 2023 CEUR-WS. All rights reserved.
