TI  - Neuro-Symbolic XAI: Application to Drug Repurposing for Rare Diseases
PY  - 2022
JO  - Lecture Notes in Computer Science (including subseries Lecture Notes in Artificial Intelligence and Lecture Notes in Bioinformatics)
DO  - 10.1007/978-3-031-00129-1_51
AB  - An emerging challenge in high stakes fields such as healthcare is to build a more transparent artificial intelligence. Among the fields which use AI techniques, is drug development, and more specifically drug repurposing. DR involves finding a new indication for an existing drug. The hypotheses generated by DR techniques must be validated. Therefore, the mechanism of generation must be understood. In this project, we focus on DR using link prediction algorithms. Link prediction consists of generating hypotheses about the relationships between a known molecule and a given target. More specifically, this PhD project aims at creating methods allowing to make transparent prediction in the context of drug repurposing but also to understand how the organization of data in a knowledge graph changes the quality of predictions. © 2022, The Author(s), under exclusive license to Springer Nature Switzerland AG.
