AB  - Large Language Models (LLMs) face limitations in specialized domains such as environmental management due to hallucinations and static knowledge. Standard Retrieval-Augmented Generation (RAG) provides contextualization through vector search but struggles with complex queries requiring structured reasoning and explainability - crucial in geospatial contexts where "where"matters. We propose a hybrid GraphRAG architecture that combines vector retrieval with a dynamically constructed Knowledge Graph (KG). By enabling LLMs to extract and link entities (e.g., regulations, project sites) within the KG, our approach enhances both semantic flexibility and structured reasoning, improving accuracy for spatially aware and regulatory queries. © 2025 Copyright held by the owner/author(s).
