AB  - As dual-supervisor cultivation and interdisciplinary integration increasingly become core models for postgraduate education in China, traditional teaching approaches face significant challenges in knowledge organization, cross-disciplinary linkage, and personalized instruction. This paper proposes an intelligent question-answering system based on knowledge graphs, utilizing agricultural engineering interdisciplinary courses as an application scenario. The system ingests scientific research manuals and textbooks from agriculture and engineering domains. Using Named Entity Recognition (NER) technology, it extracts entities and relations from textual sources, structures them into triples, and constructs an agricultural engineering knowledge graph using Neo4j. Implemented with Django for user interface and Rasa for intent recognition and entity extraction, the system integrates the knowledge graph for semantic matching and knowledge retrieval. Retrieved results are linguistically enhanced and expanded using the DeepSeek large language model to generate pedagogically appropriate, natural-language responses. Experimental results demonstrate that the system achieves high response accuracy and semantic richness within agricultural engineering education, effectively improving knowledge acquisition efficiency and educational experience in interdisciplinary contexts. © 2025 Copyright held by the owner/author(s).
