AB  - This paper proposes an intelligent piano education system (DM-LFTP) based on dynamic meta-learning and light-field haptic fusion, which achieves closed-loop control of multimodal perception, personalised decision-making and immersive interaction through a three-tier collaborative architecture The system adopts Music Transformer to construct a music theory knowledge graph (2048 nodes, 15,360 edges), combines with Conditional Variational Auto-Encoder (CVAE) to realise melodic variation generation, and innovatively designs a dual-channel co-ordination mechanism based on the cosine similarity ( =085), which reduces the potential spatial alignment error by 623% The light-field haptic fusion system achieves sub-millimetre spatial mapping (localisation error <04mm) and sub-millisecond haptic synchronisation (latency of 91ms) with the JVC D-ILA light-field engine (pixel pitch of 85m) and 100×25 piezoelectric array, with a linearity of the light-intensity-tactile-force mapping function (T(I)=0511-3 ) up to R2=097 The experimental results show that: (i) the dynamic meta-learning mechanism improves the touch-key recognition accuracy to 938% (Δ+37%, p<0001), and the rhythmic weighting steady state error is reduced by 734%; (ii) the light-field system achieves 256 depth samples at a refresh rate of 60Hz, with a crosstalk ratio of <25dB; and (iii) the overall system latency is 114ms, which enhances the real-time teaching and learning by 402% compared with the traditional scheme Clinical tests show that the trainees’ fingering accuracy is improved by 327% (582%→909%), and improvisation ability is improved by 415% (MMI index 0195→0301N-s/m) A new technological paradigm is provided for the intelligentisation of music education © 2025 Copyright held by the owner/author(s)
