AB  - Accurate time-series prediction plays a crucial role in industrial process control, where multivariate coupling, nonlinear dynamics, and inherent time delays present significant modeling challenges. In particular, moisture content prediction serves as a representative task that requires high-precision forecasting under complex dynamic conditions. To address these issues, this study proposes a hybrid prediction framework that integrates Temporal Convolutional Networks (TCNs), Transformer architectures, and Cross-Attention mechanisms for enhanced spatiotemporal feature extraction. A delay-alignment strategy is introduced to compensate for process hysteresis by aligning input-output sequences. The proposed model is validated on real-world data from tobacco moisture conditioning equipment, achieving superior performance compared to conventional approaches, with an MAE of 0.033, RMSE of 0.045, and R² of 0.91. These results demonstrate the model's capability to handle long-range dependencies, multivariate interactions, and process delays, offering promising applications in intelligent industrial process monitoring and real-time control. © 2025 Copyright held by the owner/author(s).
