AB  - [Purpose/Significance] Addressing the issue that intelligent reference services in libraries cannot directly handle specific business operations and the lack of interfaces with third-party business systems, which leads to insufficient integration of intelligent reference services with business processes, this study proposes a construction scheme for intelligent reference services based on BERT, AIML, and HTTP protocol. [Method/Process] First, a local knowledge base and AIML corpus are established, and the performance of intent classification is compared between BERT-Base-Chinese and the large language model Chinese-LLaMA-2-7b. Second, BERT-Base-Chinese is used for semantic matching in the knowledge base, AIMLBot is employed for dialogue management, and user queries are initiated to collect user information. Finally, HTTP communication technology is utilized to achieve deep integration with both local and remote library business systems. [Results/Conclusion] The study found that using BERT-Base-Chinese for intent classification achieved an accuracy of 0.958 3, while semantic matching in the knowledge base achieved an accuracy of 0.946 1. Moreover, HTTP communication technology proved to be feasible and effective for integrating local and remote library business systems. © 2025 LIS Press Co., Ltd. All rights reserved.
