AB  - Deep language model-based DTI predictors often lack integration of biological knowledge, resulting in limited interpretability. This work introduces a knowledge-enhanced DLM-DTI framework that incorporates KEGG pathways and Gene Ontology annotations into transformer-based molecular and protein representations. Benchmark results show 7 - 9% higher AUC-ROC and 9-11% higher AUPR compared to leading baselines. Case studies in oncology and cardiovascular diseases achieve AUC-ROC scores of 0.945 and 0.923, respectively, with attention weights revealing biologically meaningful pathways. The framework maintains efficiency with 0.02-second inference per pair, enabling practical application to large-scale virtual screening. © 2025 IEEE.
