AB  - This study proposes DK-POL, integrating deep reinforcement learning with dynamic knowledge graph reasoning. Through semantic alignment, dual-channel fusion, and adaptive constraint optimisation, DK-POL consistently outperforms DQN, PPA, and SCA. Task success rates reach 91% on Freebase, 94% on CompGCN, and over 80% on MAG240M, with constraint violations nearly eliminated. Under 30% feature noise, DK-POL maintains 83.8% accuracy. Reasoning analysis reveals deeper relational traversal with low overhead (4.8 ms), demonstrating strong robustness, interpretability, and scalability across diverse decision-making scenarios. © 2025 Informa UK Limited, trading as Taylor & Francis Group.
