AB  - Timely and accurate perception of the operating state of electric power switchgear is crucial for ensuring the safety and reliability of power grid systems. This paper proposes an intelligent state perception framework that combines an enhanced YOLOv11 object detection model with a domain-specific knowledge graph. The proposed approach utilizes deep learning to detect multiple visual indicators - such as circuit breaker status lights and position indicators - on the surface of switchgear equipment. The detected visual features are then mapped into a structured knowledge graph to infer the comprehensive operational state of the switchgear, including statuses such as running, maintenance, hot standby, and cold standby. Additionally, a multi-modal fusion strategy is integrated to improve the robustness and interpretability of the system. Experimental results demonstrate that the proposed method achieves high accuracy and adaptability in real-world substation environments, enabling intelligent decision-making for equipment monitoring and state analysis. © 2025 IEEE.
