PY  - 2025
JO  - 3rd International Conference on Data Science and Information System, ICDSIS 2025
DO  - 10.1109/icdsis65355.2025.11071148
AB  - This research presents a novel deep learning framework for personalized recommendation of ideological and political course resources, addressing the critical need for adaptive learning systems in ideological and political education. We propose IdeoGraphBERT, a hybrid model combining BERT's natural language understanding with graph transformer networks to analyse both textual content and conceptual relationships within ideological and political theories. The system incorporates temporal attention mechanisms to track evolving learner interests and differential privacy to ensure data security. Evaluated on a dataset of 50,000 political science resources, our model achieves state-of-the-art performance with 98.9% accuracy and 0.989 AUC, significantly outperforming text-only (BERT: 88.5%) and graph-only (GAT: 86.3%) baselines. Key innovations include cross-modal attention for ideological and political concept alignment and edge-aware graph propagation for theoretical dependency modelling. The results demonstrate that deep learning can effectively bridge the gap between ideological knowledge representation and personalized learning, while maintaining pedagogical rigor and ethical considerations. This work provides a foundation for AI-enhanced ideological and political education systems that adapt to both individual learning trajectories and dynamic sociopolitical contexts. © 2025 IEEE.
