AB  - The extraction of relationships between military entities and descriptive entities is a key task for automated construction of military knowledge graphs. This category of text unstructured imposed problems such as unfixed entity length, possibly overlong intervals between entities, and excessive pronouns. Many studies rely on traditional pattern matching and statistical learning methods. Thanks to the expansion of data volume, deep learning methods are generally used to address similar problems. However, the traditional single neural network model lacks the ability to extract the relationship information of long-interval entities and cannot tackle the above problems well. To solve these problems, a new named entity relationship extraction model called DTGCN is proposed combining dependency tree and GCN (Graph Convolutional Networks). By comparing with traditional models, the experimental results demonstrate that the method proposed in this paper can enhance F1-value by 2.28–11.11% and can provide support for the extraction of Chinese long-interval relationships. © 2022, The Author(s), under exclusive licence to Springer-Verlag GmbH Germany, part of Springer Nature.
