AB  - The huge amount of data has grown exponentially with the development of Internet technology, and we have thus entered the era of information explosion. It is very difficult to get the target information that users are interested in or need in the huge amount of data. To solve the problem of information overload, recommendation systems play an important role. At present, recommendation systems have become a popular research area and have received a lot of attention with many application areas. However, recommendation systems suffer from the problems of cold start, data sparsity and poor interpretability, and many researches have been conducted to alleviate these problems. In this paper, we first give a brief overview of recommendation systems and traditional recommendation algorithms, then summarize the improvements made by recommendation systems with the introduction of auxiliary information, and finally summarize the challenges faced by recommendation systems and give the future development hotspots. © 2023 IEEE.
