AB  - The article describes the results of the development of a software system that implements the method of finding anomalies using a neural network and their subsequent analysis based on intelligent systems. The developed system processes the initial data of the time series and outputs a set of anomaly values. The system uses neural network technologies and ontological analysis. The ontology uses a pre-designed class and SWRL (Semantic Web Rule Language) rules. Such a hybrid system can correct the problem of explainability of neural networks by linking the results to the subject area. © 2023, The Author(s), under exclusive license to Springer Nature Switzerland AG.
