AB  - In order to effectively solve the problem of information overload, different types of models can be constructed for personalized recommendation through the analysis of user commodity interaction information and related auxiliary information in e-commerce. Traditional recommendation methods cannot resolve the complex and diverse connection and transmission relationships between entities, which can be solved to a certain extent by building a knowledge graph between entities. Graph neural network enables the deep learning technology to expand on the graph structure, and further improves the accuracy and interpretability of recommendation based on knowledge graph. Aiming at the problems that the weights of nodes and relationships in the knowledge graph network are adaptive, and some non-isomorphic graphs cannot be identified and learned sufficiently, an attention mechanism is proposed to learn different weights in the network. At the same time, the minimization dominating set problem and the maximization matching problem are efficiently solved by random features. The experimental results show that for three public data sets: Book e-commerce data set Amazon book, music e-commerce data set last FM and catering review e-commerce data set yelp2018; A private data set: A comprehensive e-commerce data set after desensitization of a medium-sized e-commerce enterprise in Zhejiang, including user information, commodity information and interactive information. The performance of the proposed algorithm in recall and normalized impairment cumulative gain (NDCG) exceeds the common recommended algorithms of machine learning, deep learning and knowledge graph. © 2022 ACM.
