AB  - Knowledge graphs play a fundamental role in the downstream task composition of natural language processing (NLP). To further enhance the completeness of the knowledge graph, previous studies on entity alignment usually require a large amount of training data for each relation in the knowledge graph. However, we found that the triple of fact that some triadic instances have a relatively small sample size in the data set does not equate to their less importance. In this work, our goal is to match unseen entity pairs in the knowledge graph in a challenging environment with only a few or even zero samples of training instances. We propose a joint model of adaptive clustering algorithm and multi-kernel learning that extracts feature vectors and attribute vectors (relation vectors) of entities using an embedding model, processes entity pairs by using a modified version of the adaptive clustering algorithm and uses relationship vectors to describe unseen entity pairs in the knowledge graph by multi-kernel learning. From the experimental results, our model achieves better performance. © 2021 ACM.
