TI  - Personalized learning recommendation system based on DeepSeek algorithm
PY  - 2025
AB  - In order to enhance the personalization and accuracy of learning content recommendation on online education platforms, a personalized learning recommendation system based on DeepSeek algorithm was developed. The system adopts the method of integrating student behavior logs, knowledge point structure and teaching content embedding, and adopts a multi-expert hybrid mechanism to achieve user portrait shaping, content semantic matching tasks and multistage recommendation decision-making process. In terms of data, EdNet large-scale education data set was selected for modeling and testing. The total number of samples was nearly 200,000, including multi-dimensional features such as questions, answer performance and knowledge point association. The experimental results show that the system performs better than the existing mainstream models in core indicators such as Precision@5, Recall@5 and AUC. Precision@5 achieved 0.836 and AUC reached 0.924, which proved that the recommendation system has high performance and stability. The research conclusion shows that DeepSeek algorithm can significantly enhance the modeling ability of education recommendation system for complex behavior characteristics and knowledge structure, and lay a solid technical path and verification foundation for large-scale personalized learning services. © 2025 IEEE.
