PY  - 2023
JO  - Transactions of the Korean Institute of Electrical Engineers
DO  - 10.5370/kiee.2023.72.9.1097
AB  - Recently, as the number of organizations performing national R&D(Research and Development) projects has increased, the demand for analytics services that provide R&D information for each project organization is increasing. It is essential to identify the organization in order to provide information by changing the data built around the R&D project to the performing organization. Previously, organization identification was performed using identification codes such as business registration numbers, corporate numbers, corporate codes for system-specific management, and string match of user-entered organization names. However, the existing method does not account for user misspellings and variants, which leads to misidentification problems. Therefore, we propose SMART-ID, a hybrid system that applies semantic similarity based on Bi-directional Encoder Representations from Transformers(BERT) and string similarity based on Longest Common Substring(LCS) algorithm. SMART-ID can automate the updating of the identification information of the organizations, verify the name of the organization in R&D project data, automatically assign an organization identification code to R&D project data, and search for the organizations using text. The experimental results demonstrate the superior performance of SMART-ID on real data from the National Science & Technology Information Service(NTIS). SMART-ID will be utilized as an organization name recognition module within chatbot to provide more accurate statistics and search information by organization. © © The Korean Institute of Electrical Engineers.
