AB  - Semantic matching is a hot topic in the field of NLP. It is widely used in information matching, machine translation, intelligent Q&A, and answering system. With the rapid development of artificial intelligence, people pay more attention to friendly human-computer interaction and how to obtain accurate and effective information. Aiming at the problem of the diversity and structure of Chinese, this paper introduces the cross attention mechanism. Texts provide attention to each other, then to information retrieval. Experiments on aetc-nlp dataset show that the method is effective. © Published under licence by IOP Publishing Ltd.
