AB  - This paper proposes a visual story generation algorithm based on fine-grained visual features and knowledge graphs. The algorithm aims at how to fully mine and extend the representation of image content. This project intends to study and develop fine-grained visual feature generation algorithms based on text and word collection generation algorithms based on semantics from the visual level and high-level semantic level. Using image data containing entity associations, deep convolution learning is implemented for fine granularity. The relationship between external knowledge maps and adjacent images is expanded and enriched by using high-level semantic integration. Finally, a more complete and detailed expression of the video sequence is given. The performance of this algorithm is compared with other algorithms on VG-MSDN. The average recall rate was 62.5% and 42.6%, respectively. This new method can solve the problem of insufficient predicate information in traditional scientific knowledge and improve the scientific knowledge effect. The probability of the information predicate appearing in the prediction predicate is greatly increased.
