PY  - 2022
JO  - 2022 13th International Congress on Advanced Applied Informatics Winter (IIAI-AAI-Winter)
DO  - 10.1109/iiai-aai-winter58034.2022.00056
AB  - This paper proposes a method of heterogeneous similarity calculations for time series data comparison and its score integration for evaluating semantic similarity of human posture feature between two persons as trainee and trainer. In this method, a set of posture feature data obtained from videos of body motion of a person with superior posture and a person who want to have superior posture are used as input data. The similarity degrees between the data are calculated by multiple calculation methods using the shape and the frequency features as waves on the time-series data. A superior body motion is defined as a suitable posture from the viewpoints of mechanics, work efficiency, and aesthetics. The posture feature data consists of coordinate information of joints extracted using MediaPipe [1]. DTW (Dynamic Time Warping) [4], [5] to compare the shape feature and FFT (Fast Fourier Transform) [6] to compare the frequency feature are adopted in this time. In addition, the scores of two or more similarity measures are integrated after normalization. In the experiments, we confirmed the effectiveness and feasibility of the proposed method on flexion and extension exercises. As an application of the proposed method, we assume to be personal training at home or in the office in order to realize healthy society.
