TI  - Research on Distribution Network Harmonic Source and Weak Points Identification Based on Data Association Analysis
PY  - 2021
JO  - The 10th Renewable Power Generation Conference (RPG 2021)
DO  - 10.1049/icp.2021.2346
AB  - In the current power grid, new energy sources and non-linear loads lead to higher harmonics, making the power grid vulnerable to security and stability. This article uses the data association analysis FP-growth algorithm to track the harmonic source and week points in the distribution network. By analyzing the actual power quality data, the harmonic correlation of each monitoring node is analyzed. Frequent itemsets of monitoring nodes with high relevance in each harmonic are searched. According to the harmonic sequence relationship of each monitoring node, the proportion of the harmonic power injected by each monitoring node and monitoring node combination is calculated. The harmonic source is judge by forming theprobability function for each monitoring node. Simulations based on actual power quality data are conducted to obtain the harmonic sequence relationship and to judge the harmonic source. The effectiveness of the proposed algorithm is verified.
