AB  - Based on online monitoring data, the harmonic problem of the offshore wind farm is analyzed and studied. Firstly, the operation state of the wind farm and the harmonic emission level of the wind turbine are analyzed. Then, according to the daily statistical data of wind farm harmonics, histogram analysis and quantification of statistical indicators such as skewness and kurtosis are carried out to grasp the statistical data distribution characteristics of wind farm harmonic current. Finally, based on the minute-level data of typical days of harmonic problems, the correlation analysis between the harmonic data and the wind farm operation state is carried out to clarify the corresponding relationship between the harmonic anomaly and the wind farm operation state, which provides new ideas and directions for harmonic management.
