AB  - This study presents a hybrid text summarization model that addresses the challenge of processing large textual datasets with enhanced efficiency and accuracy. The approach integrates Latent Semantic Analysis (LSA), PageRank, and the Longformer neural network to improve the quality of generated summaries. LSA identifies key themes and reduces dimensionality, ensuring essential content is captured while avoiding unnecessary details. PageRank ranks critical information, and the Longformer's sparse attention mechanism effectively processes long sequences, overcoming limitations of traditional models like BERT and GPT when handling lengthy documents. Evaluated using precision, recall, and F1 score metrics, the model demonstrates superior performance in retaining essential information and producing coherent, high-quality summaries across various document sizes and complexities. The results suggest the model's scalability and adaptability for different real-world applications, including academic research, legal document processing, and journalism. Future efforts will focus on further optimizing the model's computational efficiency and expanding its utility across diverse text domains.
