AB  - A knowledge graph (KG) is playing an important role in representing structured knowledge for all kinds of intelligent systems. Though there exist a variety of KGE models, the majority of them are static in nature that is they are not adaptive, do not have contextual awareness and are not scalable to complex real world settings. In this paper, we propose a novel dynamic Knowledge Graph embedding framework which composed of five core components namely: real-time context ingestion, dynamic graph storage, contextual embedding with attention mechanism, transparent Neural Symbolic reasoning engine, and governance module for compliance and trust. The system uses embedding's that are efficiently updated with new incoming knowledge, interpretable predictions, and scales to large enterprise datasets efficiently. Results of this evaluation are superior, as measured on standard benchmarks FB15k-237, WN18RR, and YAGO3-10. In terms of MRR, the model proposed here obtains scores of 0.492, 0.463, and 0.521. Hits@10 reaches 72.5%, 68.3%, and 75.9%, outperforming the state-of-the art baselines such as TransE, DistMult, and CoKE. It confirms that the framework can make accurate predictions, can scale, and reasons transparently for dynamic knowledge applications.
