AB  - The rapid evolution of cyber-physical infrastructures introduces challenging tasks in maintaining predictive resilience and adaptive cognition under a highly dynamic, heterogeneous, and privacy-restricted environment. Traditional distributed learning systems lack semantic and cognitive depth for situational awareness to interpret the evolving contextual patterns and mitigate the unpredictable anomalies in real time. This work addresses this gap through a Neuro-Semantic Federated Meta-Optimization Framework, which effectively integrates quantum-enhanced computation with deep neurocognitive intelligence for predictive anomaly cognition. The proposed system leverages semantic knowledge graphs and neuro-symbolic encoding at the edge layer for enabling semantic-aware reasoning fused with probabilistic quantum subspace modeling for efficient distributed learning. A federated meta-optimizer dynamically reconfigures the local models by means of cross-domain knowledge distillation with an aim to enhance adaptability and convergence speed. The novelty lies in quantum-assisted meta-learning with neuro-semantic cognition for self- evolving, context-aware optimization in cyber-physical ecosystems, thereby fostering sustainable development toward an autonomously intelligent infrastructure.
