AB  - The paradigm shift in the hospitality industry is taking place with the development of smart systems that can help provide hyper-personalized experience to guests. In this paper, a new model and framework, namely Context-Aware Neuro-Symbolic Adaptive Experience Model (CANSAE) is presented to pursue better contextual responsiveness, interpretability and emotional interpretation of hospitality settings. To attain adaptive and privacy-compliant personalization, the proposed framework will combine neuro-symbolic reasoning, federated preference learning and multimodal emotion recognition. CANSAE combines deep neural networks and symbolic logic to provide transparency in its decisions besides addressing dynamism in customer preferences. The model utilizes federated learning to introduce the insights of distributed sources of data without violating the privacy of users whereas emotional context incorporation is a method of understanding real-time affective cues to customize ambiance and service delivery. Moreover, one can refer to a continuously developing knowledge graph, which is updated every time there is an interaction to help the system to anticipate and satisfy the needs of guests in advance. Reinforcement learning also helps to refine the individualization of a recommendation, and increase the user satisfaction scores. Through experimental simulations, CANSAE has been shown to be more adaptive, interpretative and more engaged with the guest than the current AI-based means of personalization. This piece of work constitutes a platform to emotion-sensitive and contextually relevant hospitality ecosystems that have the power to restructure user experiences in a sustainable and human-focused way. The suggested CANSAE model had an overall accuracy of 97.4%, indicating exceptional optimization of individualized experiences in the hospitality industry.
