AB  - Telecom network resource management systems are primarily built on relational databases, leading to data fragmentation and semantic isolation across different professional domains such as transmission, access, and core networks. This paper proposes an intelligent resource management framework that integrates Knowledge Graphs (KG) and Large Language Models (LLM). Relational data are transformed into a semantic knowledge representation that unifies multi-domain resources and dependencies. The LLM operates as an AI agent that leverages this knowledge for semantic query, reasoning, and decision support, while also performing data validation and graph optimization to enhance overall data quality. This bidirectional enhancement—where the knowledge graph supports reasoning and the LLM refines the knowledge—enables a closed-loop intelligent management system. Application results in telecom resource operations, including transmission and cloud domains, demonstrate significant improvements in efficiency, accuracy, and interpretability.
