AB  - For natural language processing knowledge graph construction, Chinese dictionary entry-level hierarchical systems' dispersion and low coupling hinder downstream tasks. This paper proposes the TFC-TEGCN algorithm to fuse entry-level systems into a dictionary-level one. It introduces a “Golden Tree”, uses BERT and cosine similarity for textual similarity, multi-layer GCNs for local structure, an improved Transformer for global relations, and a DAG module for acyclic structure. Experiments on self-built and public datasets validate its effectiveness in solving data quality, entity linking, and global modeling issues, laying a foundation for graph fusion and cross-level relation completion.
