AB  - Chinese text matching is an important task in natural language processing research, but the current techniques have problems in text feature extraction, such as insufficient word information extraction and lack of deep information in graph convolution networks. In this paper, we propose a model MFG-R for Chinese text matching with multi-information fusion graph embedding and residual connection. The model fuses the word embedding representation of the text obtained by graph convolution network with character-level information and word weight information to extract text features. At the same time, in order to perform deep interaction matching, we construct a word-level similarity interaction matrix between text pairs, and build a text interaction and feature extraction model based on residual network on this basis. Experiments show that MFG-R has excellent performance on two common Chinese datasets, Ant Financial Question Matching Corpus(AFQMC) and Large-scale Chinese Question Matching Corpus(LCQMC).
