AB  - ICH requires rapid, accurate CT-based diagnosis, but varied hemorrhage traits challenge automated detection. Traditional deep learning struggles with local-global feature balance and AI interpretability. Our hybrid framework integrates multi-scale convolution, attention, and knowledgedriven inference, using 3D RDC for local texture extraction with anatomical priors and ASA for efficient global feature aggregation via anatomy-guided self-attention. On the ICH2023 dataset, it achieves 94.1% DSC (8% improvement) and 32% better clinical consistency, with strong generalization. This interpretable framework connects deep learning and expert diagnosis, with future work on ontologies and feedback for better decision-making.
