AB  - Machine Reading Comprehension (MRC), as an important research direction in the field of Natural Language Processing (NLP), aims to enable computers to automatically answer questions by understanding natural language text. However, traditional MRC systems based on pre-trained language models (such as BERT, RoBERTa, etc.) often lack the capability to model external knowledge, making it difficult to handle questions that require background knowledge or reasoning. This paper proposes a Chinese MRC model enhanced with Knowledge Graphs (KGs). By introducing an entity-level knowledge enhancement mechanism, semantic information from the knowledge graph is interactively fused with textual semantic representations, thereby improving the model's reasoning and comprehension abilities. The proposed model is applied to the AI tour guide scenario for the Chinese Ethnic Culture Park. A custom question-answer dataset is constructed, and experiments are conducted using CMRC2018 and DRCD Chinese datasets for validation. Experimental results show that the proposed model achieves improvements of approximately 3.7% and 2.9% in F1 and Exact Match (EM) scores, respectively, compared to the traditional RoBERTa-MRC model, demonstrating the effectiveness of knowledge enhancement for Chinese question answering tasks.
