AB  - Biomedical question answering remains a challenging task due to the complexity of clinical knowledge and the limitations of general-purpose large language models (LLMs) in providing accurate, domain-specific responses. We introduce Chimera-3X, a hybrid cognitive engine that orchestrates multiple specialized LLMs (DeepSeek, BioGPT from Microsoft, and Exone 3.0 from LG), each fine-tuned and adapted as an independent medical sub-toolkit. Chimera-3X integrates external biomedical knowledge graphs such as UMLS, SNOMED CT, and Wikidata via retrieval-augmented generation techniques, enhancing the system's factual accuracy and reasoning capabilities. Each engine processes clinical queries independently while the orchestrator coordinates their outputs, leveraging SPARQLbased queries to ensure precise knowledge retrieval. Preliminary evaluations demonstrate significant improvements in clinical answer accuracy, coherence, and interpretability compared to standalone LLM approaches. We propose an architecture that provides a scalable, transparent and effective framework for biomedical consulting, advancing the integration of knowledgedriven AI in healthcare applications. Code and Resources: https://github.com/marwan8086/Chimera-3X
