AB  - To address the deficiency of Chinese medical question-answering systems in entity recognition, intent understanding, and complex question processing, this paper proposes a method integrating semantic parsing and knowledge graph reasoning. This method also integrates a weighted fusion mechanism of confidence matching and similarity calculation to implement fuzzy retrieval, and introduces the RetrievalAugmented Generation (RAG) mechanism to generate supplementary answers when knowledge graph reasoning results are insufficient. Experimental results show that the proposed method achieves higher accuracy and F1-score than the baseline models in both the named entity recognition task and the intent recognition task. Finally, it exhibits high stability and flexibility in multi-turn question-answering, verifying its effectiveness and scalability.
