AB  - In recent years, personalized learning platforms gained prominence for delivering adaptive education but effectively recommending relevant learning resources while addressing data sparsity, cold-start problems and semantic understanding remained an existing challenge. Existing recommendation models often depend on collaborative filtering or deep learning which limited adaptability and alignment with pedagogical objectives. Therefore, this research proposes Hybrid Knowledge-Enhanced Personalized Learning Recommendation Model (HK-PLRM) for improving personalization by combining attention-augmented collaborative filtering, knowledge graph embeddings, and incremental deep learning. Initially, student and teacher models are constructed from multi-modal behavioral, assessment and instructional data for capturing learning preferences, performance and pedagogical intent. Then, knowledge graph module encodes semantic relationships between resources, exercises and knowledge points by using graph neural networks by enabling context-aware recommendations. Next, hybrid recommendation module predicts preference scores by fusing collaborative filtering, knowledge graph and deep learning outputs with attention-based weighting. Finally, cloud-based platform continuously updates models by using incremental learning, ensuring real-time adaptation to evolving learner behavior and enabling scalable, mobile access to personalized learning resources. From the results, the proposed HK-PLRM achieved better results in terms of Mean Absolute Error (MAE) of 0.72 and Root Mean Suare Error (RMSE) of 1.03 when compared with existing models.
