AB  - Knowledge Graph Embedding (KGE) is important to the value of the Knowledge Graph (KG) in its application field. Currently, neural network-based models achieve the most advanced performance. However, these models rarely consider the potential information between entities and relations in KGs, and also suffer from the problems of complex structure and high consumption of computing resources. In this paper, we propose the simple and efficient model PartDensE by using dense network, combining specific sharing layer and relational awareness layer. Specifically, our model learns all entities and relationships individually and can mine hidden features to enrich global information. Also, learn all the information based on each relation and be able to accurately establish associations between entities and relations. PartDensE can capture global and local features and displayed and hide information, retaining as much valuable information as possible. We evaluated PartDensE with 4 indicators across on two baseline datasets. Numerous experimental data prove the effectiveness of our model.
