AB  - In the context of intelligent recruitment, traditional person-job recommendation approaches struggle to effectively capture the complex interaction intents between users and job positions. To address this challenge, this paper proposes a Knowledge Graph Enhanced Bidirectional Intent-Aware Person-Job Recommendation Approach(KG-BIAM). The proposed method first constructs a domain-specific Knowledge Graph to enable multidimensional representation of user and job intents. Second, a cross-intent attention mechanism is designed to model the interaction between user intent and job intent, thereby enhancing matching accuracy. Finally, a multilayer graph convolutional network(GCN) is employed to aggregate semantic information from the Knowledge Graph and further refine the intent representations. Experimental evaluations are conducted on a real-world data set obtained from "ZhaoPin.com". The results demonstrate that the proposed method outperforms existing baseline models in key performance metrics such as AUC, F1-score and Balanced Accuracy, thereby validating its effectiveness.
