AB  - This paper proposes a comprehensive deep learning-based system for plant leaf disease detection, classification, and control with the in-built pest recommendation feature. The model utilizes various best available architectures: U-Net for precise leaf segmentation, EfficientNetV2B0 for stable feature mapping, Relational Graph Convolutional Networks (R-GCN) for disease classification, and Vision Transformer (ViT) for pest mapping. The proposed pipeline begins with U-Net-based image segmentation of high resolution and EfficientNetV2-L feature extraction for pattern detection of disease. R-GCN applies a knowledge graph approach to disease classification based on their usual presentations, while ViT produces disease-pest mappings through attention. Experimental results confirm the system’s improved performance with 97.5% accuracy in classification of different disease classes. The in-built pest suggestion module provides contextually relevant treatment suggestions by associating detected illnesses with relevant pest control practices. The work addresses the imperative demand for computer-aided disease diagnosis in precision agriculture, which can reduce chemical use while enhancing yields through timely intervention practices. The system’s modular design allows it to be scaled to suit different agricultural environments and types of crops, a huge step towards sustainable agriculture technology.
