AB  - Our research is based on the YOLOv12 target detection algorithm to achieve accurate recognition of students’ classroom behavior, and real-time detection and generation of Classroom Thermal label data. The detection results are input into Qwen model and RAG (retrieval enhanced generation) framework for collaborative analysis. RAG’s educational domain knowledge base is used to enhance context understanding and realize quantitative evaluation of teaching interaction and personalized strategy generation. The research focuses on the various indicators of YOLOv12 model for target recognition in the classroom scene, as well as the optimization process of Qwen-RAG model in the dynamic updating of behavior rules and the generation of real-time suggestions. The closedloop from visual perception to teaching decision-making is realized through algorithm cascade, and finally interpretable behavior analysis report and teaching optimization suggestions are output, providing core algorithm support and credible reference for data-driven classroom teaching.
