AB  - To address the fault diagnosis challenges of flexible welding assembly stations in automotive body-in-white production, this paper proposes a novel diagnostic framework that integrates knowledge graphs with Bayesian inference. The proposed approach overcomes the limitations of traditional methods, which struggle to effectively incorporate equipment mechanisms and often lack sufficient reasoning capabilities. Leveraging historical failure data, a BiLSTM-CRF model is employed to identify fault-related entities, while the causal relationships among these entities are extracted using a BERT-based method. A comprehensive knowledge graph is then constructed, encompassing equipment mechanisms, process parameters, and fault propagation pathways. This knowledge graph is subsequently mapped to a Bayesian network, enabling quantitative analysis of fault propagation and root cause tracing through probabilistic inference. The proposed method significantly enhances fault diagnosis efficiency and offers an interpretable and adaptable solution for complex industrial scenarios.
