AB  - Relation extraction in specialised domains like medicine is challenging due to semantic complexity and class imbalance. MedREX, a novel joint entity-RE model, addresses these issues using Erlangshen-MegatronBert-1.3B as its encoder for rich contextual representations, enhanced by an additional Transformer encoder layer for long-range dependency modelling. Its dual-biaffine attention-based decoder factorises extraction into three subtasks: entity mention identification, subject-object alignment for relation classification, and tail alignment for relational structure completion. Focal Loss and adversarial training (Fast Gradient Method) mitigate class imbalance and improve robustness. Experiments on the CMeIE-V2 dataset show MedREX outperforms baselines, with improved F1 score, precision, and recall, confirming its effectiveness.
