JO  - 2025 IEEE 3rd International Conference on Sensors, Electronics and Computer Engineering (ICSECE)
DO  - 10.1109/icsece65727.2025.11256976
AB  - With the rapid growth of online learning data and multimodal physiological signals, accurately extracting learners’ cognitive and affective features has become a core challenge in educational AI. This study proposes an end-to-end dynamic closed-loop optimization framework. First, a spatio-temporal attention module is embedded into a convolutional neural network. This fuses behavior logs and physiological signals. It yields high-dimensional profiles of cognitive load, emotional engagement, and knowledge structure. Next, dynamic weighted KNN applies exponential decay and differentiation amplification on these profiles and feedback signals. It achieves real-time adaptive clustering. Finally, Dijkstra’s algorithm locates an initial global path on the weighted knowledge graph. Then, multi-objective functions and an ant colony optimization strategy refine the path continuously. Refinement uses prediction confidence and online feedback. Experiments on large-scale datasets of online behavior and physiological signals show that our framework outperforms linear models, standalone deep models, and stepwise methods. It yields higher prediction accuracy, path efficiency, learning gains, and user satisfaction. Moreover, the real-time feedback loop improves robustness to learner heterogeneity and noise. Finally, we discuss challenges in cross-domain deployment, multimodal integration, and online implementation. We suggest future work on automated hyperparameter tuning, model lightweighting, and interpretability. Our framework offers guidance for personalized learning path planning in smart education.
