AB  - The growing complexity of legal systems and the diversity of regional languages in India have made legal guidance less accessible to the general public. This paper introduces IPC Section Classifier an AI-driven platform designed to interpret user-submitted crime descriptions in multiple Indian languages and provide relevant sections of the Indian Penal Code (IPC). Leveraging a multilingual transformer-based model, semantic similarity matching, and real-time translation, the system bridges linguistic barriers to legal awareness. It also integrates text-to-speech functionality for auditory guidance. The paper outlines the system architecture, model training, and performance evaluation based on accuracy and relevance. Our results demonstrate that the proposed solution improves public access to legal information through an intelligent, language-agnostic interface.
