AB  - Traditional proofreading of official documents struggles to meet modern office requirements for semantic accuracy, format compliance, and efficiency. To address this challenge, this paper presents an intelligent proofreading framework that integrates fine-tuned large language models with LangChain workflow orchestration, Retrieval-Augmented Generation (RAG) for knowledge enhancement, TF-IDF semantic matching, and rule- and terminology-based validation. A domain-specific corpus was constructed from high-quality institutional texts, and Low-Rank Adaptation (LoRA) was applied for efficient model tuning. Experimental results show that the proposed framework outperforms mainstream models such as ChatGPT-4, DeepSeek, DouBao, and Qwen3-32B, achieving an average correction accuracy above 80%, an over-correction rate below 10%, and a 30% reduction in response time, while maintaining a Stability Index over 0.9. These results demonstrate that combining knowledge enhancement with rule constraints effectively improves the robustness and reliability of large language models for intelligent official document proofreading.
