AB  - This work presents an intelligent recruitment support system that extends beyond candidate ranking to deliver comprehensive skill-gap analysis, enabling candidates to identify areas for improvement while providing recruiters with actionable insights. By integrating automated data extraction, semantic similarity matching, and rule-based decision mechanisms, the system reduces recruiter workload, enhances shortlist accuracy, and promotes a fair and transparent evaluation process. The approach addresses a critical need in modern recruitment by balancing automation with equity, ensuring equal opportunities while optimizing time and organizational resources. Owing to its adaptable architecture, the solution is applicable across corporate hiring, campus placements, and professional job platforms. Future enhancements include the incorporation of advanced transformer-based deep learning models, multilingual résumé processing, and real-time recruiter dashboards. Overall, the system supports Sustainable Development Goal 8 (Decent Work and Economic Growth) by fostering efficient, unbiased, and inclusive hiring practices.
