AB  - Fragmented Traditional Chinese Medicine English knowledge hinders global dissemination. To address this, this study proposes an intelligent algorithm-driven framework to construct a comprehensive TCM English knowledge graph. The method integrates NLP and machine learning: Bi-LSTM+CRF for entity recognition, CNN for relation extraction, and a rule-neural two-stage optimization that reduces invalid relations by 15%. Structurally, the graph is organized around a 5-layer TCM-theory-based ontology, integrating multilingual terminologies and hierarchical relationships. An application system enables intelligent querying, context-aware retrieval, and both rule-based and machine learning-based reasoning. Experiments on a large dataset show a 30% higher accuracy in semantic matching and knowledge inference than keyword-based systems, with 88.6% semantic retrieval accuracy and 91.3% disambiguation for key terms. Results demonstrate that the approach enhances TCM knowledge access precision and efficiency while resolving crosslingual challenges. By establishing a computable knowledge infrastructure, it provides robust technical support for TCM internationalization and more accessible global medical communication.
