AB  - In multilingual translation of technical documents, terminological consistency significantly affects both the professionalism and comprehensibility of the target text. To address the insufficient terminology support in existing translation systems, this paper proposes and implements an intelligent terminology recommendation system tailored for real-time technical document translation. The system integrates modules for terminology recognition, contextual matching, candidate recommendation, and translation injection. Leveraging deep learning architectures and semantic vector techniques, the system provides real-time suggestions. Experimental results demonstrate that the system significantly enhances the accuracy and consistency of terminology translation, offering reliable support for human–machine collaborative translation. This system represents a step forward in AI-powered translation support tools.
