DO  - 10.1109/icimia67127.2025.11200536
AB  - Complicated eligibility rules, disjointed information as well as language barriers makes it difficult in most cases to navigate government welfare schemes with its citizens. Traditional online websites and applications often do not offer customized instructions, language inclusion, and easy interaction floors, which leads to a low level of usage of the necessary public services. To overcome these drawbacks, an intelligent recommendation system has been created to utilize Retrieval-Augmented Generation (RAG), semantic vector similarity search and multilingual conversational artificial intelligence. The system derives semantic embeddings via Facebook AI Similarity Search (FAISS) to facilitate effective information retrieval and comprises Google Generative AI to take advantage of natural language understanding. LangChain is used to support dynamic, contextually aware conversation, and FastAPI is introduced as the framework to permit an easy flow of integration. It was developed in multiple languages with real time translation between English and Tamil to provide ease of use by different groups of users. The system provides a single API that can recognize the intent of the user, check his/her eligibility and suggest the appropriate schemes in a language that adjusts to the user. The method fosters digital inclusions, simplifying delivery of public services and facilitating access to government welfare programs on equal basis.
