AB  - With the acceleration of globalization, massive multilingual translation corpora in distributed storage environments present core problems such as strong data heterogeneity and low cross-node retrieval efficiency. To this end, this study proposes a cross-node retrieval optimization framework based on a hybrid index structure. Firstly, this paper designs a multi-dimensional feature coder for semantic units. Then, this paper constructs a distributed hierarchical index structure based on improved LSH (Locality-Sensitive Hashing). Finally, a dynamic load balancing algorithm based on spark is developed. Experimental results show that on the Europarl and UN Parallel 2.1 TB multilingual corpus, the Top-10 retrieval accuracy is as high as 91%, and the Hybrid scheduling strategy achieves 800 QPS throughput under 1500 concurrent conditions. In the above data conclusions, this framework performs well in retrieval accuracy, real-time responsiveness and high concurrent throughput, providing scalable technical support for real-time retrieval of cross-border language service systems.
