AB  - With the improvement of the reliability requirements of power production and the strict requirements of state Grid Corporation on the power supply service quality, the traditional power operation and maintenance mode has been difficult to meet the current demand. Therefore, this paper proposes to use knowledge graph technology to integrate, analyze and visualized power data to improve the efficiency and accuracy of power operation and maintenance. By constructing the multi-source heterogeneous information model and the deep semantic matching model of the electric power system, the fusion of heterogeneous data and feature extraction are realized. The power data knowledge graph is built, taking the equipment fault alarm event as an example, and the application effect of the power data knowledge graph in real-time monitoring and early warning, fault location and maintenance decision is shown.
