DO  - 10.1109/ssim59263.2023.10468710
AB  - The rapid progress of Artificial Intelligence (AI) has gained widespread attention worldwide, and its applications in industries have inspired a strong interest in the semantic relationship. As one of the hotspots of AI research, Chinese international core words have been valued and favored by scholars. An in-depth exploration was conducted in this study for the semantic connections of Chinese international core words in AI with a literature review. There were disagreements on the definition of word concepts in AI, which directly affects theoretical innovation and application. With the continuous development of science and technology, numerous vocabularies are added, and their meanings are constantly changing. At present, the academic community still lacks an in-depth understanding of the relationship between the Chinese International Core Vocabulary and AI so it is necessary to research it. Combining the historical evolution of terms, the semantic meanings at different times and contexts were investigated to provide a basis for further study. Existing studies were limited at the lexical level and lacked in-depth exploration from the syntactic perspective, thus failing to demonstrate the complex semantic relationships among Chinese international core vocabulary. In this study, the Semantic Relational Model of International Chinese Core Vocabulary in AI Scenarios (SRMCCV) was developed based on linguistic theory and computer processing technology. Statistical analysis methods such as word frequency statistics were used to explore the semantic logic of frequently used words and analyze relevant literature and new corpus. The model revealed the potential connections between words and semantic interactions in AI. The results can be used to improve the quality of international Chinese language teaching.
