AB  - Ontology technology is the core technology of semantic web, which can describe information well and retrieve described information through querying knowledge warehouses, greatly improving retrieval efficiency and accuracy. Distributed retrieval is the process of combining heterogeneous data stored on a large scale through a network, utilizing the processing capabilities of multiple machines to centrally solve collaborative indexing and retrieval problems, and ultimately forming a logical whole. Firstly, the semantic search architecture was studied; Then, the AMIE+rule inference algorithm was studied, including rules and functions, the process of AMIE+mining algorithm, and evaluation criteria; Next, the process of rule-based reasoning algorithm was studied; Finally, experimental analysis was conducted, and four algorithms including Tableau algorithm, Apriori algorithm, Rete algorithm, and AMIE+algorithm were selected for comparison, demonstrating the superiority of AMIE+algorithm and providing a basis for subsequent software system development.
