AB  - Table column matching is a crucial preprocessing task in data integration and governance, aimed at identifying semantically corresponding columns across different data tables, which is of great significance for breaking down "data silos". However, existing methods face challenges in accuracy and robustness when dealing with complex scenarios such as semantic heterogeneity in column names and sparse, variable column values. This paper proposes a column matching method that dynamically processes column text information with hybrid probability features. We design a dynamic Top-K column value selection strategy to adaptively construct column text representations that maximize information content. Furthermore, we introduce hybrid matching probability features, combining Equivalence Link Matching Probability (ELMP) based on value overlap with Semantic Link Matching Probability (SLMP) based on semantic embeddings, providing the model with dual decision evidence at both statistical and semantic levels. Experimental results on both Chinese and English datasets demonstrate significant superiority over various pre-trained baseline models.
