AB  - To tackle the "same-type, different-ID" puzzle and missing serial data in automatic 3-D-model-to-ledger linking for substation assets, we present an pipeline that couples nameplate reading with semantic matching. First, PP-OCRv5 detects, dewarps and recognizes characters from high-resolution nameplate textures on 3-D equipment shells. Then, paraphrase-multilingual-MiniLM embeds both recognized text and ledger records into a shared vector space for similarity ranking. To counter power-specific noise such as scrambled word order, synonymous abbreviations and mis-printed numbers, we boost number weight, maintain an in-domain synonym dictionary with shape-based error correction, and encode segments in an order-invariant manner. Cross-validation on 459 ledger entries shows 86.1 % hit-rate, robust to order shifts, functional aliases, multi-phase splits and OCR typos, enabling direct binding of 3-D models to ledger primary keys and offering a low-maintenance, high-efficiency solution for digital operation & maintenance of power-grid equipment.
