AB  - As power grid construction scales up and intelligent transformation accelerates, traditional cost management methods for distribution network engineering have gradually exposed problems such as low efficiency, dependence on manual experience and scattered data. Therefore, this article proposes a multi-modal intelligent cost research method for distribution networks. This involves researching the development of a unified feature representation and fusion mechanism for text, images, and structured data to enable the automatic parsing, logical verification, and parameter comparison of cost documents. Based on this, a modular cost framework is formed and, through typical engineering parametric modelling and knowledge base accumulation, the standardization and transparency of cost management are promoted. Results show that this method can significantly improve cost preparation and evaluation efficiency, with a problem detection rate of over 95 %. This article's innovation lies in introducing multimodal data to the field of distribution network engineering costs and constructing a full-process system covering everything from data parsing and module generation to intelligent evaluation and decision support. This provides power grid enterprises with new ideas and technical paths for achieving cost reduction and efficiency improvement.
