JO  - Proceedings of the 2024 International Symposium on Integrated Circuit Design and Integrated Systems
DO  - 10.1145/3702191.3707668
AB  - This paper presents a knowledge graph-enhanced learning recommendation system driven by deep learning, aimed at generating personalized and adaptive learning pathways. The system integrates the structural representation of knowledge graphs with the predictive power of graph attention networks and transformer models to address the limitations of traditional recommendation methods, such as static pathways and limited adaptability. By leveraging knowledge graphs to encode hierarchical and semantic relationships and using deep learning to model sequential learner interactions, the system dynamically generates context-aware recommendations. Experimental evaluations on a large-scale educational dataset demonstrate significant improvements over baseline models, achieving higher engagement scores, knowledge retention, recommendation accuracy, and pathway diversity. The results highlight the effectiveness of combining structured knowledge representations with advanced learning models to enhance learner outcomes. This research provides a robust and scalable framework for personalized education, with potential applications in diverse adaptive learning environments.
KW  - Adaptive Learning, Deep Learning, Knowledge Graph, Learning Recommendation System, Transformer Model
