AB  - This study addresses the challenges of low efficiency and structural difficulties in tacit knowledge mining within enterprises by proposing a Hybrid tacit Knowledge Mining Framework based on Large Models(HKMF-LM). By integrating Natural Language Processing (NLP), Knowledge Graphs (KG), and Reinforcement Learning (RL) techniques, we construct a methodology consisting of “data preprocessing - domain adaptation and parameter optimization - knowledge graph construction - dynamic inference.” Firstly, a knowledge graph is built using internal enterprise data such as documents, meeting minutes, and employee knowledge. Facts, relationships, and attributes from the knowledge graph are embedded into the large model. By combining text data with structured knowledge graphs through a multimodal learning approach, the model can process and comprehend different forms of data simultaneously. Experimental results demonstrate that this framework significantly outperforms traditional methods in terms of accuracy, recall, and user satisfaction, providing a novel technological pathway for enterprise knowledge management.
KW  - domain fine-tuning, dynamic inference, knowledge graph, large model, tacit knowledge
