PY  - 2025
JO  - Proceedings of the 9th International Conference on Electronic Information Technology and Computer Engineering
DO  - 10.1145/3766671.3766864
AB  - With the continuous expansion of the asset scale of power grid enterprises and the in-depth promotion of market-oriented reform, financial risk management plays a more and more critical role in guaranteeing the sustainable development of enterprises. The traditional financial risk assessment methods are difficult to adapt to the complex and changing financial environment due to the problems of isolated indicators, unclear causality, and low degree of intelligence. For this reason, this paper proposes a grid financial risk assessment method that integrates knowledge mapping and Bayesian network. Firstly, based on the financial data and business process information of power grid enterprises, a financial risk ontology is designed, and a domain knowledge graph for power grid finance is constructed. Subsequently, a Bayesian network risk inference model is constructed to effectively model the causal relationships and probabilistic dependencies between various risk factors. Finally, empirical analyses are carried out through the actual data of a regional power grid company to verify the advantages of the proposed model in terms of risk identification accuracy, reasoning interpretability and warning timeliness.
