AB  - Knowledge Representation Learning (KRL), also known as Knowledge Graph Embedding, is an important field in KG research that deals with knowledge acquisition, representation, and inference. However, current KRL faces challenges in learning entity representations in Zero-Shot scenarios. To address this, the ZFRL model is introduced. It efficiently handles entity and link prediction in an open-domain knowledge graph using two components: a structured knowledge embedding layer and a novel attribute encoding layer. Experimental results on an open-domain knowledge graph dataset show significant improvements in entity and relationship prediction accuracy. The ZFRL model effectively links newly added entities in a KG, supporting KG completion tasks.
AU  - Li, Tong and Zhang, Xingliang and Wu, Chao and Yang, Funing and Yang, Yongjian
