PY  - 2025
JO  - Proceedings of the 9th International Conference on Electronic Information Technology and Computer Engineering
DO  - 10.1145/3766671.3766867
AB  - The huge number of courses on online education platforms leads to information overload and selection difficulties for learners. Traditional methods such as collaborative filtering are difficult to capture dynamic interests and ignore knowledge coherence. In this paper, we propose the LSTM-KGRec model, which combines LSTM and knowledge graph to optimize the dynamic interests and knowledge coherence through user behavioral time-series modeling and dual-strategy recommendation mechanism. Experiments show that the NDCG@10 of LSTM-KGRec reaches 0.79, which is 16% and 10% higher than that of collaborative filtering and RNN, respectively, and effectively improves recommendation dynamics and knowledge coherence. Furthermore, ablation experiments verify the necessity of each module, and comparative analysis of recommendation performance across different scenarios provides a more comprehensive reference for personalized learning path planning. These comprehensive evaluations underscore the robustness and practical applicability of LSTM-KGRec in diverse educational settings.
KW  - Knowledge Graph, LSTM, LSTM-KGRec
