TI  - FMIQA: A multimodal integrated QA Robot with considerable intelligence
PY  - 2025
JO  - Proceedings of the 2024 8th International Conference on Electronic Information Technology and Computer Engineering
DO  - 10.1145/3711129.3711334
AB  - With the tremendous necessity of multimodal application services, we have devised an integrated four-levels of question and answering (QA) Robot to handle a wide range of automatic tasks ranging from language, words, voice, image, and so on. The intelligent QA Robot, FMIQA, firstly analyze and normalize the corresponding input queries from the users, and then categorize the application areas of the tasks. After the aforementioned two-levels of operations, FMIQA has identified the intention of multiscale tasks. FMIQA then moves forward to the third phase to use the multiple structure of data storage and deals with the information tasks generated from the second-level phase. Through multiple rounds of queries, FMIQA obtains the final answer and analyzes the forms of output information. In the fourth-level phase, FMIQA aligns the form of input and output, and then provides the corresponding form of the answer. The information processing with four-levels allows FMIQA to have less querying and searching time, and it has higher precision and correlation in terms of the answers to the queries.
KW  - Four-level QA Robot, multimodal query analysis, multiple structures of data storage, multiscale intention identifications
