AB  - To improve the extraction efficiency and visualization of construction safety knowledge, this paper combines knowledge graph technology with construction safety domain, and proposes a basic framework of construction safety knowledge ontology based on the evolution logic of safety events according to the characteristics of knowledge. Considering two types of safety knowledge carriers and data sources, text and image, a knowledge graph is designed to contain text semantic features and image features, and the knowledge services based on different dimensional knowledge queries are validated in the experiments. The results show that the BERT-BiLSTM-CRF algorithm can be used to extract entities in text, and YOLOv5-FastPose can extract excavator poses from images. This paper verifies the applicability of knowledge graphs for safety knowledge mining, visualization and services.
