TI  - Distant supervision relation extraction of combination bag with hierarchical attention
PY  - 2023
JO  - Proceedings of the 2023 15th International Conference on Machine Learning and Computing
DO  - 10.1145/3587716.3587726
AB  - Nowadays, most advanced methods based on distant supervision relation extraction can largely reduce the cost of manual annotation. Despite the fact that the reduction of noisy effects between sentences has been extensively studied, less attention has been paid to the removal of inter-bag noise. To address this issue, this paper presents a selective attention network with a combination bag for relation extraction under distant supervision. First, our model adopts a similarity-based inter-bag attention module to calculate scores for the bags in the bag group. Then the bag feature vectors in this bag group are incrementally combined according to the highest to lowest score to form a combined feature vector set. Finally, the highest scoring combined feature vector is used as the feature vector representation of the bag group. The proposed model can minimize the influence of noise bags and take advantage of the semantic information of positive bags. The experimental results on the New York Times dataset show that our proposed model with combination strategy outperforms some of the state-of-the-art methods in relation extraction under distant supervision.
