AB  - Addressing the challenges in tourist review sentiment analysis, including the complexity of comment sequences, difficulty in capturing contextual semantics, and the intricacy of identifying domain-specific vocabulary, this paper proposes a novel model that integrates an attention mechanism with Whole Word Masking BERT (WWM-BERT) and Bidirectional Long Short-Term Memory (Bi-LSTM). The proposed model leverages WWM-BERT's word-level masking strategy to optimize semantic extraction in comments, effectively capturing specific tourism terminology. Meanwhile, the integration of an attention mechanism with Bi-LSTM enhances the understanding of long- and short-term dependencies within the sequence of tourist reviews, thereby refining the model's sentiment comprehension and accuracy. Experimentation, based on crawled tourist user comment data, is conducted and compared with other models. Results indicate that our model achieves an impressive accuracy rate of 92.5% in identifying user sentiment on the test set, outperforming alternative models.
